Ensure data security and integrity all while providing  the required support to maintain the student information  system (Banner by Ellucian) in good operational state, as well as all associated components of the Oracle database system;
Complete all analytical tasks required for the development, maintenance and improvement of the student information system, including technologies based on Oracle;
Monitor and ensure the requirements and interdependencies of supported versions of software product used are compatible, for example Banner, Oracle, Argos, FormFusion, JAVA and OS versions of MS Windows and Linux;
Contribute to the planning of projects involving the student information system upgrades, as well as performing the necessary software installations and system configurations associated with these projects, including technologies based on Oracle;
Regularly verify the data backup and restore procedures and the disaster recovery procedures for the student information systems, as well as analyze and fine tune the system performance;
Provide support for the productivity tools Argos and FormFusion (by Evisions) associated with the student information system;
Provide support for the integration of the student information system (Banner) with the document management system (ImageNow by Lexmark);
Act as the lead and contact person in resolving technical problems with the various solution providers such as Ellucian, Oracle, Evisions and others;
See to the continuous improvement of the security policies, according to industry best practices;
Stay up to date on new information technologies;

Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science along with relevant experience;
Demonstrate significant work experience in the installation, configuration and maintenance of Oracle database systems and support tools including, but not limited to:
Oracle Relational Database management system;
Oracle application server (Fusion Middleware) with components: WebLogic, Forms/Reports and WTier;
Oracle Enterprise Manager and other surveillance tools for the Oracle environment.
Demonstrate significant working knowledge of ERP programming languages, messaging and development environments;
Demonstrate good time management and change management skills;
Be someone who takes initiative, is dynamic, with strategic and critical thinking skills;
Demonstrate an ability to adequately judge priorities of multiple projects and make necessary follow up efforts in a high-pressure environment;
Demonstrate the ability to complete tasks requiring attention to detail;
Demonstrate a self-teaching approach in the learning of new technologies associated with Oracle database management and the student information  system (Banner);
Demonstrate the ability to work independently as well as collaboratively;
Have excellent knowledge of written and spoken French;
Have a good knowledge of written and spoken English;

Assets:

Knowledge of Ellucian software (Banner);
Oracle certification (OCA);
Knowledge of Oracle Database Appliance platform;
Knowledge of open source technologies such as Tomcat server, Groovy and Grail as well as JasperReports;
Understanding of the university context;

